node.text:
An orca during sunset in Alaska via @marysmark 🐋 Swipe to see all the photos and tag a @nature lover!

The killer whale or orca (Orcinus orca) is a toothed whale belonging to the oceanic dolphin family, of which it is the largest member. It is recognizable by its black-and-white patterned body. A cosmopolitan species, killer whales are found in all oceans and most seas in a variety of marine environments, from Arctic and Antarctic regions to tropical seas; they are absent only from the Baltic and Black seas, and some areas of the Arctic Ocean.

📸 @marysmark
📍 Alaska

node.text:
@Nature paradise vibes 🐠 Situated in the Atlantic Ocean, The Bahamas is a tropical archipelago with almost one thousand islands. 🇧🇸

Did you know the story behind the sunken plane in the first shot? Read this: “This plane was owned by Pablo Escobar during the 1970’s smuggling era. It crashed when the pilot, high on his own cargo, missed the runway and ended up in the water. While the actual story is likely a lot less interesting, it still makes for a fun place to snorkel!"

From 1 to 10, which capture is your favorite? Who would you love to explore the @nature’s Bahamas underocean with? 🤿

📸 @jess.wandering @everchanginghorizon @matt.venturing 
📍 Bahamas

node.text:
When a city becomes your boulder ⛰ Bouldering is a form of free climbing that is performed on small rock formations or artificial rock walls without the use of ropes or harnesses. While bouldering can be done without any equipment, most climbers use climbing shoes to help secure footholds, chalk to keep their hands dry and to provide a firmer grip, and bouldering mats to prevent injuries from falls. Unlike free solo climbing, which is also performed without ropes, bouldering problems (the sequence of moves that a climber performs to complete the climb) are usually less than 6 meters (20 ft.) tall.

📽 @oliver_thorpe
📍 Aarhus, Denmark

node.text:
Would you dare to walk on this Via Ferrata? 😳 

The new Signora Delle Acqur, in the Ruzza river, is a highly emotional and spectacular via ferrata that gives you unforgettable emotions; the sight embraces whole Trentino, but keeping fixed on the track too.

Recommendation:
Avoid the queue: purchase online your ticket and go directly to turnstile. Choose the stage and pay with your credit card. You will receive by email your ticket (you can print the ticket or save it in your smartphone), scan it on the orange scanner on the turnstile located at the gates of the lift.

📽 @niklaskoessel
📍Trentino, Italy
